      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " etc.) Pilate did not suppose that the Jews would demand any very severe punishment to be inflicted. He ought not to have asked. It would have been safer to have simply dismissed the prisoner; cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 18:14-16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".—",
        "children": []
